**PPF, EPF, and NPS** are India's three main government-backed retirement instruments, each with different tax treatment, liquidity, and return profiles. PPF: 7.1% p.a., fully EEE tax status (Exempt-Exempt-Exempt). EPF: 8.25% p.a., EEE for ≤5 years, then partially taxable. NPS: market-linked (8–10% typical), EET (taxable at withdrawal on 60% corpus).
